Industrial Bank of Korea provides various banking products and financial services to individuals and corporate customers. It operates through seven segments: retail banking, corporate banking, money market, credit card operations, foreign exchange, and others. The company accepts various deposit products, such as demand, instalment, time, and certificates of deposit, as well as savings and current accounts; and offers retail loans, mortgage loans, overdrafts, and other credit facilities. It also provides credit cards; credit information services; investment banking products and services; bancassurance; and annuity, retirement, and pension and life insurance products Industrial Bank of Korea was founded in 1961 and is headquartered in Seoul, South Korea.

Taiwan Cooperative Financial Holding is a financial holding company. The company operates its businesses primarily through investment and management of its subsidiaries: Taiwan Cooperative Bank, Taiwan Cooperative Bills Financial Corporation, Taiwan Cooperative Securities, and others, which are involved in banking, bill finance, credit card, trust, insurance, security, future, venture capital and other financial activities. The company was established in 1946 and is headquartered in Taipei, Taiwan.
column36: Chung-Dar Lei, chairman, has said that the bank sees Phnom Penh as a hub from which it can expand north and south in Cambodia, extending its reach in the emerging market.

column6: Kent International, Inc. designs and manufactures bicycles for adults, youth, and kids. It also offers specialty bikes, cycling accessories and tools, cycle parts and maintenance items, as well as cycling helmets for adults, youth, toddlers, and children. The company was formerly known as Philkam Cycle and changed its name to Kent International, Inc. in January 1958. Kent International, Inc. was founded in 1947 and is based in Parsippany, New Jersey.

column6: Prestige International provides business process outsourcing services such as roadside assistance, property assistance, insurance BPO, warranty, IT solutions, customer support and provides temporary workers. The company was formed in 1986 and is based in Tokyo, Japan.

Shenzhou International Group, an investment holding company, engages in manufacturing, processing, and selling knitwear products in China on an original equipment manufacturer basis. It offers casual wear, sports wear, and lingerie. It is also involved in the import and export of commodities; clothing detection; print and sale of knitwear products; retail business; and property management activities. The company exports its products to Japan, Europe, Asia-Pacific, and the United States. Shenzhou International Group was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Ningbo, China.

Onward Holdings manufactures men's ready-made suits, women's, and children's wear. The company has its own brands, Onward and KUMIKYOKU. The firm also manufactures sports goods, books, stationery, cosmetics and art decoration. It was founded in Tokyo, Japan.
TripFactory is a travel agency that helps users find new travel locations and book their next stay. The company was established in 2013 and is headquartered in Bangalore, India.

South Korea-based KB Financial Group is a financial holding company that provides various banking and related services. Its remit includes commercial banking, asset management and life insurance. The company engages in computer system development, system maintenance and information technology outsourcing services. The company was founded in 2008 and is headquartered in Seoul, South Korea.

Hoang Anh Gia Lai (HGAL), through its subsidiaries, engages in developing apartments for sale and lease in Vietnam. It operates through segments which include real estate, production, trading and services, construction, power, mining and plantation. It is also involved in the manufacture and trade of furniture and granite products, construction business, the management of properties and trading of goods, developing and operating hydropower plants, building and operating hotels and resorts, sports and entertainment activities, and exploiting and selling iron ore. HGAL was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Pleiku City, Vietnam.

South Korea-based KB Financial Group is a financial holding company that provides various banking and related services. Its remit includes commercial banking, asset management and life insurance. The company engages in computer system development, system maintenance and information technology outsourcing services. The company was founded in 2008 and is headquartered in Seoul, South Korea.

QLM Label Makers manufactures labels and tags. The company offers product, thermal overprinted, chemical and weather resistant, industrial, digital, food/beverage, laser and computer, personal/healthcare, thermal, variable data, and custom printed and blank labels, as well as barcodes on food storage containers. It also distributes thermal printers, digital colour printers, ribbons, and touchscreen computers, as well as provides graphic design services. QLM Label Makers was incorporated in 1961 and is based in Brisbane, Australia.

column6: Yisheng Group., a biopharmaceutical company, researches, develops, manufactures, and markets immuno-oncology products and vaccines. It offers YS-ON-001, an investigational biological product that demonstrates immuno-modulating effects, such as induction of anti-tumour cytokines, activation of NK cells, regulation of macrophage polarization, and suppression of regulatory T cells for the treatment of advanced solid tumours. Yisheng Group was founded in 2002 and is based in Beijing with operations in China, the United States, and Singapore.

DragonEx is a cryptocurrency exchange platform. The firm was founded in 2017 and is based in Singapore.

Chengdu Bayi Furniture Stock Co., Ltd. was founded in 1998. The Company's line of business includes the manufacturing of house furnishings, such as blankets, bedspreads, sheets, table clothes, towels and shower curtains. The company is based in Chengdu, China.

Join.In Hospitality Management Co., Ltd. is the exclusive licensee of Tonino Lamborghini brand in the field of the hospitality industry, specifically hotel operation and management for mainland China, Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan, Japan, and British Columbia, Canada. The firm is based in Shanghai, China.

column6: Kinokuniya Company Ltd. operates stores that sell various products to customers in Japan and internationally. The company offers Japanese/foreign books, journals (electronic journals), magazines, CD-ROMs, audio-visual software products, stationery items, and educational and library equipment/systems. It also provides electronic information services; publishing services; audio-visual software production services; bibliographic database production services; and theatre and art gallery management services. The company was founded in 1927 and is based in Tokyo, Japan. It has stores in Japan, Singapore, Taiwan, Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, the United States, Australia, the United Kingdom, and the United Arab Emirates.

SolarHome Pte. Ltd. leases solar energy units for rural off-grid households in Southeast Asia. It installs integrated solar energy and appliance units in customers' homes, and offers 'rent-to-own' plans of energy service subscription. The company uses the microfinance structure, Pay-As-You-Go (PAYG), which enables users to pay a monthly fees comparable to their current expenditure on legacy energy sources. The company was founded in 2016 and is based in Singapore. The company also has operations in the Philippines, Cambodia, Myanmar, and Indonesia.
Fourtitude Asia is a cloud platform developer. It was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Petaling Jaya, Malaysia.

column6: Kingsmen C.M.T.I. Public Company Limited engages in interior design and decoration, and exhibition businesses in the Asia-Pacific and the Middle East. It offers retail and corporate interior services, including retail interiors, roll-outs, retail fixtures, corporate interiors, and restaurants; exhibitions and events, such as custom-designed stands, official shows, events, pavilions, suites and chalets, and rental services; thematic and museums comprising theme parks and attractions, galleries and visitor centers, and museums; and event management services. The company was founded in 1989 and is headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand.

column6: Innity Corporation Berhad, an investment holding company, provides interactive online marketing platforms and technologies for advertisers and publishers. Its interactive online marketing solutions include display advertising network, video advertising network, self-service advertising platform, performance and engagement based advertising, programmatic buying, and real-time bidding solutions.The company was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Petaling Jaya, Malaysia.

column6: Kameda Seika is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of snack products. The company operates in three business segments. The snack segment is engaged in the manufacture, package converting and sale of snack products. The freight transportation and storage segment provides transportation and storage services. The others segment is engaged in the sale and repair of automobiles, as well as the development and sale of computer software and the designing and supervision of equipment. As of March 31, 2010, the company had 11 subsidiaries and two associated companies. The company was founded in 1957.

Hongdou Group Co.,Ltd. engages in the clothing, machinery, rubber, textile, printing and dyeing, biotechnology, real estate, and financial businesses. The company was founded in 1984 and is based in Wuxi, China.

Evergreen Marine, together with its subsidiaries, engages in marine transportation, shipping agency, and container distribution businesses. It provides cargo loading and discharging, terminal, and container shipping services; invests in transport-related business, container yards, and port terminals; and manufactures dry steel containers and container parts. It offers container loading, discharging, storage, repair, cleaning, and inspection services; and inland transportation, stevedoring, and logistics support services. In addition, the company provides agency services dealing with port formalities; leases real estate properties; and invests in and leases operating machinery and equipment of port terminals. The company was founded in 1968 and is headquartered in Taipei, Taiwan.

Sumitomo Group is an integrated trading company that operates in the metal products, transportation, construction, energy, electronics, chemicals, and other sectors. Sumitomo Group is based in Tokyo, Japan, and was established in 1919.

FELDA Holdings, through its subsidiaries, engages in palm oil business. The company provides plantation development and management, oil palm processing, replanting, agricultural and plantation advisory, and cattle rearing services, as well as produces, refines, markets and packages oil based products. It is also involved in breeding and trading biological assets; animal food production; and fresh meat and carcass supply. FELDA Holdings was founded in 1988 and is based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The company is one of several private corporate entities launched by the Federal Land Development Authority (FELDA).

CJW International Co., Ltd. designs and sells fine jewellery products. The company offers diamonds, jade, and coral jewellery. It is also involved in the wholesale and retail of tobacco, beauty, and other products. The company was founded in 1978 and is based in Taipei City, Taiwan.

Green Leader Holdings Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the distribution of information technology products in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It operates through Systems Integration Services and Software Solutions, Mining Operation, Coal Operation, and Cassava Starch Operation segments. The Systems Integration Services and Software Solutions segment provides information technology products, systems integration, technology, software development, Internet, software solution engineering, and maintenance services. The Mining Operation segment engages in the exploration and development of coal deposits, and sale of coking coal, as well as the provision of geological survey services. The Coal Operation segment provides coal trading and logistics services. The Cassava Starch Operation segment engages in cultivation, processing, and sale of cassava starch. The company also engages in energy development and equipment trading activities; and sale of equipment and services. Green Leader Holdings Group Limited has a strategic cooperation framework agreement with Guangxi State Farms Mingyang Biochemical Group, Inc. for the mutual development of cassava industry project in Cambodia. The company was formerly known as North Asia Resources Holdings Limited changed its name to Green Leader Holdings Group Limited in September 2017. Green Leader Holdings Group Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

The Dai-ichi Life Insurance Company provides life insurance products to individual and corporate customers in Japan and internationally. The company offers individual life insurance products and annuities, sells non-life insurance products and savings-type products through financial institutions, such as banks and securities companies. It also provides group life insurance products, group term life and medical care insurance products, which help employees prepare insurance by themselves and group annuities. Further, it provides various investment products, such as domestic bonds and stocks and foreign securities. The company was founded in 1902 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
Toong operates co-working spaces throughout Vietnam and it also has a presence in Laos and Cambodia. The firm was founded in 2015 and is based in Ha Noi, Vietnam.

JACCS Co., LTD. is a consumer credit company. The Company provides consumer instalment credits, credit cards, loan guarantees and loans. Jaccs also operates car lease and art rental businesses and have subsidiaries in U.S., Singapore, and Hong Kong. The firm was founded in 1954 and is based in Tokyo, Japan.

column6: Duan & Duan is one of the most well-known local law firms in China. The firm has become well recognized as the pioneer and leader in international legal services for both foreign companies entering China and PRC companies doing business abroad. One of the first privately owned law firms in China. Duan & Duan is now staffed with 50, more than 20 of whom are experienced attorneys and counsels. The firm's advanced management, and its ability to straddle legal systems, languages and cultures has led to the representation in China of a number of the worlds' largest Fortune 500 companies. Since 1993, the firm has represented these companies as they have entered the Chinese marketplace, and has grown as their clients' business in China has expanded. Duan & Duan has also grown in conjunction with their representation of many large Chinese companies in their business dealings abroad. Sido Muncul provides herbal medicines, cosmetics, and foods and beverages related to health in Indonesia and internationally. The company produces approximately 80 types of medicines consisting of ethical products, OTC products, food supplements, and medical herbs. Its products include Anacetine, a medicine to reduce fever; Combicitrine, a medicine for bacteries/worms removal; Berlosid, a medicine for gastric pains; Anabion multivitamins for children; Suprabion multivitamins for adults; and Telon Oil. The company also manufactures herbal extracts. In addition, it offers confectionary products, energy and health drinks, and other products. Further, the company is involved in commerce and land transportation activities. PT Industri Jamu dan Farmasi Sido Muncul Tbk is headquartered in Semarang, Indonesia, and was founded in 1940.

United Motor Works (Siam) Public Company Limited imports and distributes automotive service equipment. The company is the sole distributor of Briggs and Stratton diesel generator from the United States and "McKay" plough disc from Australia. The firm is based in Bangkok, Thailand and was founded in 1947.

Omni Navitas partners with commercial and industrial property owners, agricultural land and farm owners, and government agencies to implement revenue-generating solar solutions for private and public institutions, with no cost to the owner. The company is based in Boston, Massachusetts.

Mobile World Investment Corporation engages in trading, repair, and maintenance of phones in Vietnam. It offers phones, information technology equipment, cameras, digital equipment, electronic equipment, household appliances, and related accessories. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.

CloudFlare provides solutions that protect and accelerate websites online. It offers the CloudFlare content delivery network, CloudFlare optimiser and CloudFlare security, as well as security protection services; and detects new attacks that arise against websites on its network. CloudFlare was incorporated in 2009 and is headquartered in San Francisco, California, US.

Wah Sun Hand-Bag Factory Co. Limited was founded in 1985 and is based in Hong Kong. The Company's line of business includes the wholesale distribution of women's, children's, and infants' clothing and accessories.

column6: Profood International Corporation is a leading manufacturer of dried fruit.  The company was founded in 1980 and is based in Cebu City, Philippines.

It offers phones, information technology equipment, cameras, digital equipment, electronic equipment, household appliances, and related accessories. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.

Luk Fook Holdings, an investment holding company, is engaged in sourcing, designing, wholesaling, trademark licensing, and retailing of various gold and platinum jewellery, gold ornaments, and gem-set jewellery. The company is involved in gold bullion trading; wholesaling polished diamonds; property holding; and the provision of quality examination services, as well as the authentication of gemstones. In addition, it provides software development and Internet-related services. Luk Fook Holdings was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Jordan, Hong Kong.

Bank of South Pacific Limited provides banking products and services to individual and business customers in Papua New Guinea, the Fiji Islands, Niue and the Solomon Islands. Its personal banking products and services include transaction and savings accounts, term deposits, home loans, personal loans and international banking services. The company also provides business banking products, such as international banking services, overdrafts, instalment loans, lease financing, business asset loans, bridging loans, merchant services, payroll services and term deposits for small, medium and big businesses. Founded in 1957, the company is based in Port Moresby, Papua New Guinea.

column6: Vietnam Rubber (Industry) Group provides technical, advisory, and consultancy services to the rubber industry. Its services enable the rubber industry to control and monitor the quality of rubber, rubber planting materials, and rubber products; develop, transfer, exploit, and promote research findings; sell and export crude natural rubber; supply and import inputs; and export machinery and spare parts. The company also produces technical specified and constant viscosity rubber; and latex, which is used to produce medical gloves and condoms. Vietnam Rubber Industry Group was founded in 1995 and is based in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.
